  "prompt": "Do chipmunks bite people?",
  "response": "Yes, chipmunks can bite people, although it is relatively uncommon. Like many small animals, chipmunks may bite if they feel threatened, cornered, or are handled improperly. Generally, chipmunks are more likely to avoid humans and will typically only bite in self-defense. If bitten by a chipmunk, it is important to clean the wound thoroughly and monitor for signs of infection, as with any animal bite. If the bite is severe or raises concerns, seeking medical attention is advisable.",
